Description: This project analyzes customer purchase behavior to group them into distinct segments using K-Means clustering. The goal is to uncover patterns for targeted marketing strategies.

Objectives of the Project
Perform exploratory data analysis (EDA) on customer transaction data.

Apply K-Means clustering to identify customer segments.

Visualize clusters and interpret their characteristics.

Provide actionable business insights for personalized marketing.

Tools and Libraries Used
Programming Language: Python 3.9+

Libraries:

Pandas (data manipulation)

NumPy (numerical operations)

Matplotlib/Seaborn (visualization)

Scikit-learn (K-Means, StandardScaler, silhouette_score)

Jupyter Notebook (interactive development)

